## Symptoms and outcomes by menstrual cycle week

Decreased appetite and increased depression were positively correlated with menstruation, whereas infection, mood swings, swelling, and headache scores were higher during menstrual cycle week 4. Changes in productivity were not significantly different across the menstrual cycle.

