```

# **Limitations**

Hormone therapy was initiated 5 days into the first menstrual cycle week 1, potentially limiting exchangeability between the first week 4/week 1 observations and subsequent week 4/week 1 observations. In addition, confounders included a multi-day family medical emergency during week 1 of the second menstrual cycle (first week 1), which resulted in atypical sleeping, eating, anxiety, and depression, and possibly, post-exertional malaise the following week.
